Job Description: Testers Northern Netherlands

Job Description:
We are looking for Testers for our office in Groningen! If there's one thing that's certain in software development and innovation, it's that everything needs to be tested, and preferably as smartly as possible! Software, hardware, processes, you name it! To achieve this, CGI is looking for Testers in all areas and sizes - Test Automation engineers, Performance engineers, Service Virtualization engineers, Test Architects, and 'die hard' all-around testers. Are you experienced? Great! Do you want to learn the profession? Perfect! Are you a student looking for an internship? No problem!

What will you be doing:
In the CGI team in Northern Netherlands, we will work for our government clients to ensure that the software of the Netherlands is effectively and thoroughly tested in all aspects. You will develop yourself into a top Tester in one of our areas: Test automation, Performance testing, Test architecture, or Functional testing. If you have a lot of experience, you can work as a test coordinator or test manager. You will work on optimizing test processes, delivery processes, and quality, and you will enjoy mastering new test tools. Previous experience with Robot Framework and/or Selenium and/or Tosca and/or Loadrunner is a plus. Work experience in Agile/DevOps teams is also a plus.

What you bring:
You are proficient in both Dutch and English and navigate easily within CGI and the client organization. You have good analytical skills and are a structured worker. In addition, you have:
- A completed HBO/WO education with a strong IT component;
- Affinity for software engineering;

It is also a plus if you:
- Have experience with Robot Framework and/or Selenium and/or Tosca and/or Loadrunner;
- Have basic test certification: ISTQB Foundation and/or TMap NEXT Foundation;
- Have PSM1;
- Have knowledge of agile/scrum, continuous integration, deployment, and delivery;
- Have knowledge of Azure DevOps, Jira, Confluence, Jenkins, Bitbucket, and Git;
- Have knowledge and experience with XML and SoapUI;

Where will you end up:
You will be working in a diverse and close-knit team. In your role, you will work on projects that have an impact on the daily lives of millions of people. Each of our clients has its own challenges. What they all have in common is that they need to transform their services and operations to keep up with market developments. We help our clients accelerate this transition.

What we offer:
We offer you a permanent contract so that you have job security right away. Part-time work, for example, 32 or 36 hours per week, is negotiable. We offer this flexibility gladly, also regarding hybrid work. Furthermore, we consider it important that everyone feels ownership of their own work. Literally ownership, as at CGI you have the opportunity to become a shareholder and share in our successes. We also value that you stay inspired, do the things you are passionate about, and continue to develop. Through our CGI Academy, you can follow various relevant training courses. In addition, knowledge sessions are regularly organized by the test practice.

What else do we have to offer:
A place in a close-knit team of professionals where we share the responsibility for the development of our clients and employees together. A team with which we are creative and innovative, exceed customer expectations, and make a name for ourselves within CGI and beyond. In short, a role in our CGI story! Are you ready to be part of our story? Apply now! We will contact you as soon as possible. If you have any questions about the position, please contact Wyger Leijstra via the "Apply now" button on this page or at +31627272337. If you have any questions about the application process, please contact Lisa van der Kooij via the "Apply now" button on this page or at (088) 564 0000. We do not work with external recruitment agencies. Acquisition based on our vacancies is therefore not appreciated!

Tasks and responsibilities:
- Build with and on each other
- Technology is the heart of our and our customers' digital transformation, but our people are the heart of business success. As a member of CGI, you are naturally a specialist in your field and a reliable advisor to your client. You work together with your colleagues to achieve tangible and sustainable results that keep the Netherlands - and far beyond - running. Your work has an impact every day. You are a 'member' because you are a shareholder and owner of CGI. Together, we build a company we can be proud of. Since 1976, this has been our dream and it has brought us to where we are today: one of the world's largest independent IT and business consulting services providers. At CGI, we know that diversity is essential. That's why we strive for an inclusive culture in the workplace, where there is room for everyone. Both with us and with our clients. We fight for equal opportunities and want all our employees to succeed and grow. We are happy to help with that. Ready to be part of our success story? Become a member of CGI! Here, your ideas and actions make a difference.

Company Description: CGI is one of the world's largest IT companies. Our people keep the Netherlands running. Government agencies, banks, infrastructure organizations, and manufacturing companies are CGI's customers. We work on projects that impact the everyday lives of millions of people. The strength of CGI lies in excellent teamwork. It has always been the foundation of our projects. Achieving successes together by getting the most out of each other. It's almost becoming a given, although it's not. Our secret? The coherence between expertise and the interaction between colleagues is the recipe for our success. It's no wonder that we score high in customer and employee satisfaction. That says it all! When you start your story at CGI, you not only improve the lives of other people, but CGI does the same for you. We are committed to your personal growth and well-being. Whether you're a starting or experienced IT professional, CGI offers opportunities for you to develop and grow. Our small, self-managing teams keep you inspired and help you to do what you do well, even better. With over 76,000 experts worldwide, we provide a vast source of knowledge, experience, and support for you to rely on.

What you are going to do 
Would you like to contribute to the pharmaceutical sector as an operator in the 3-shift system? And do you have an affinity for technology and a completed MBO 3 or 4 education? Then come and work at Astellas in Meppel. Interested? Then read on! 

At Astellas Pharma Europe, we are looking for Operators. As an Operator, you work together with your colleagues in the 3-shift system. Together with your colleagues, you ensure that the medication in tablet form is packaged in blisters. As an Operator, you are responsible for keeping the production and packaging lines running and for managing the employees working on the line. At the beginning of the line, the tablets are placed in the blister and then closed. The blisters are then placed in a box with the corresponding package insert. As an Operator, you ensure that the correct packaging and package inserts are in the machine. During the process, quality control is automatically performed, and if there are any deviations, the blisters and boxes are removed from the process. At the end of the line, there is a production worker responsible for manual packaging, who ensures that the boxes are packed in larger boxes. Further responsibilities in your role as an Operator: 
- Ensuring that the line keeps running;
- Solving minor malfunctions and supporting the technician with major malfunctions;
- Checking that the correct medication and packaging are in the line;
- Setting up and converting the lines;
- Ensuring that the work environment is always safe and tidy. 

About the company 
You will be working for our client, Astellas Pharma Europe, located in Meppel. This organization is a young and progressive company that is committed to improving the health of people worldwide. Astellas is one of the top twenty pharmaceutical companies in the world. The organization provides innovative medications for patients in urology, organ transplantation, dermatology, and cardiology. Astellas is known as a good employer that invests in its employees and values continuous development. You can grow into a Pharmaceutical Expert. You will receive thorough training from an experienced employee, and it is always possible to ask questions or obtain additional information. 

Job requirements 
You are someone with an affinity for technology who would like to work as an Operator in a pharmaceutical factory in the 3-shift system. You can work safely and have technical insight. In addition, you have:
- Completed MBO 3 or 4 diploma;
- Proactive and communicative skills;
- Own transportation. 

What we offer you 
We offer you a well-paid job as an Operator for a longer period of time in the 3-shift system at Astellas in Meppel. You will work full-time in a fixed team. Astellas also offers various career opportunities. Furthermore, we offer you:
- A salary between €15.10 and €20.90 gross per hour excluding shift allowance;
- A shift allowance of 21.5% over your salary in the 3 shifts;
- Accrual of vacation days and 8.33% holiday allowance;
- Travel allowance according to the Astellas collective labor agreement. 

Do you see yourself working as an Operator at Astellas in Meppel? Then don't wait and apply now! For further questions/information, please contact Danique at 0522-750580.

Text: "What you are going to do. Are you the top performer with procurement experience that we are looking for? Do you want to work 32-40 hours, do you live close to Nijmegen, and are you looking for a job in the area? Maybe we have the vacancy for you. What tasks would you perform as an all-round purchasing employee:

Commercial: you support the development of the marketing plan of various suppliers;
Projects: you participate in various commercial projects and support process improvements;
Administration: you create new items in the database, process and distribute changes in condition agreements, and prepare price lists;
Communication: you have informative contact with suppliers and you are the point of contact for product and price information for your colleagues;
Analysis: you support Category managers in various matters concerning assortments and suppliers and provide reports;

About the company. A brief summary of the fast-growing company with many growth opportunities, Quantore Nijmegen-Beuningen:
Quantore is one of the largest players in the field of office supplies. More than 400 independent office supply retailers are affiliated with the organization. We also provide procurement and logistics for a number of large retail customers. The core activity is wholesale trade in office supplies with a turnover of 150 million euros and an assortment of 24,000 items. In total, about 200 people work at Quantore. Our core values are: Honesty, Responsibility, Cooperation, Development, and Customer and Member Orientation.

Job requirements. What do you bring with you:
You have knowledge of Excel and preferably experience with Microsoft Dynamics AX or D365;
You are extremely accurate, with a sense of administrative processes;
You have good communication and commercial skills;
You want to work between 32 and 40 hours;
You are available for 32/40 hours;
You have an MBO+ or HBO level of education with a commercial and/or administrative orientation;
If you can answer yes to everything, then read on quickly to find out what you can expect from us.

What we offer you. If you are our hero, don't wait any longer and read what you will get:
Temporary contract with the prospect of a permanent appointment;
Of course, you also build up holiday pay, paid leave, and a pension with us! Travel allowance of €0.19 per km;
An attractive salary, depending on your knowledge and experience, between €2,191 and €2,841, with additional interesting bonus scheme;
A versatile position with development opportunities and freedoms, in an ambitious and large organization with an informal working atmosphere;
A job for 32 to 40 hours. Can you already see yourself working at Quantore? Don't wait any longer, apply today! We will contact you within 48 hours to discuss the possibilities together."

What you are going to do 
For this job vacancy, we are looking for a combination of commercial and technical insight. Do you have this? Then we are looking for you! Balink is located in Heerenveen and has an exciting technical and commercial job opening. Balink produces innovative glass products. Your role is also very important as you will be responsible for the entire process from beginning to end. For example, you will take the order and ensure that the order reaches the supplier for the necessary materials. You will also have a lot of contact with your colleagues in the factory. Furthermore, you will arrange the transportation to the customer. In short, a versatile and challenging position. Your daily tasks consist of the following:
- Making and following up on quotes;
- Keeping track of and checking the bookkeeping;
- Maintaining contact with customers;
- Answering technical questions from customers;
- Handling administrative tasks. 

About the company 
Balink highly values customer satisfaction! There is plenty of room to take risks and think outside the box. Balink is an innovative producer of glass products. The team has a serious working atmosphere but there is also room for humor. Intense periods of activity are interspersed with moments of utmost concentration, in short: a dynamic work environment! The location is in Heerenveen and is easily accessible from Leeuwarden, Drachten, and Sneek. 

Requirements 
In addition to a commercial drive, you have a good technical insight. You will also be dealing with technical questions and be responsible for the entire order process. You are driven to successfully handle and complete each order. Furthermore, you have:
- Demonstrable experience in a similar role;
- Completed a MB-4 education;
- Strong numerical skills: you must be able to quickly calculate and prepare quotes for customers;
- A customer-oriented attitude: the customer is king! 

What we offer you 
This is a commercial role in which you will largely work independently. Within this role, there is plenty of room for your own input. The intention for this position is that you will have a long-term job with the possibility of a permanent contract with Balink itself. Additionally, it is a full-time position with working hours from 08:30 to 17:00. Furthermore, we can offer you:
- A gross monthly salary between €2,500 and €3,200 (depending on experience);
- A full-time challenging position in day shifts;
- Travel allowance of €0.19;
- 8.33% holiday allowance;
- Access to over 1000 training courses and education programs via Start People. 

Are you enthusiastic about this position? Apply now! The procedure is as follows:
- We will contact you within 2 working days;
- If we see a match, we will schedule an intake interview with you;
- If the impression is positive, we will introduce you to the organization itself;
- The organization will determine whether they want to invite you for an interview on location! 

Do you have any questions? You can reach us at the phone number 0512-532483, via drachten@startpeople.nl, or send a message to 0628399028.

What you will do
Would you like to work in the most beautiful and enjoyable production environment in Ede? Do you enjoy successfully operating production installations and improving the process? Do you also want to continue developing and have technical insight? Then you are the person we are looking for! For our valued relation in Ede, we are looking for an operator in the 3-shift system. Together with your colleagues, you are responsible for packaging our delicious juices and sending them to our distribution center. You are responsible for operating the machines and production lines. You work in small teams within a machine product group, where you support and assist each other. Your responsibilities include the following:
- Ensuring that the machines run correctly and following guidelines in the process;
- Ensuring the safety of your colleagues and yourself;
- Monitoring the quality of the process through checks;
- Adjusting the machines for different products;
- Cleaning the machines and recording process data and deviations;
- Using your own knowledge, skills, and insight daily. You also identify areas for improvement and propose solutions. In short, a very diverse and challenging role. Interested? Respond quickly and who knows, you might soon start working as an operator in the 3-shift system at this amazing company in the food industry!

About the company
Our relation's daily task is to make the tastiest fruity drinks. You may know them from brands such as DubbelFriss, Taksi, Appelsientje, and many others. They have been doing this for over 50 years in their own production environment in Ede. This makes working here so special. They have everything in one place: from product development, marketing, production to distribution (and everything in between). They love making quick decisions, taking on responsibility, and having fun and variety every day. You will do all of this with a friendly team that likes to work together. They are open from Monday to Friday and the shifts for the 3-shift system operator are as follows: 
- Early shift: 6:30 am - 2:30 pm
- Late shift: 2:30 pm - 10:30 pm
- Night shift: 10:30 pm - 6:30 am
It is easily accessible from Arnhem, Amersfoort, Apeldoorn, and Veenendaal.

Requirements
What do we want to see in our new 3-shift system operator?
- You have intermediate vocational education (MBO) level of thinking and working;
- You have process technical insight and knowledge;
- You bring enthusiasm, a proactive work attitude, and a focus on results;
- You are a team player, but you can also work independently;
- You identify areas for improvement, take responsibility, and initiate discussions;
- You have computer skills and are accustomed to working according to quality standards;
- You place great importance on safety and want to continue developing;
- You speak, write, and understand Dutch well and have strong communication skills.

What we offer you
- A position in the 3-shift system with a guaranteed minimum shift allowance of 19.58%;
- A good salary according to the Collective Labor Agreement for the dairy industry;
- A group of fun and enthusiastic colleagues;
- A full-time workweek of 36 hours and a permanent position.
And let's not forget: unlimited access to the most delicious juices during working hours!

Text: "What you are going to do Do you enjoy processing additives into a liquid or powder? Are you a starting or experienced operator with insight into technology, and do you ensure the realization of planned production in the desired quality on a daily basis? Can you set up the machines well and mix and blend the liquids/powders in the right way? Then continue reading about the position of operator (day shifts) in Deventer. As an operator (day shifts), you will work at this company in Deventer where they convert additives into liquid or powder through a production process. The liquids and powders you will produce are mainly used in the paint and printing ink industry, but also in the food and cosmetic industry. As a (process) operator, you are responsible for producing products (semi-finished products) in accordance with work instructions and you control/supervise the entire production process. Quality and safety are always a priority. In addition, your tasks include: Monitoring and controlling the production process; Resolving technical malfunctions or reporting them to the production manager; Thinking, optimizing, and improving (work) processes; Adjusting in a timely manner when necessary through taking samples that are analyzed by the lab; Making adjustments to optimize the quality after checking the sample; Moving raw materials by forklift. We would like to have a cup of coffee with you to tell you more about the company, daily tasks, and the team you will be working in. Interested? We are happy to assist you. Feel free to call Start People Enschede for more information at 053 4814600. Would you rather send a WhatsApp message? You can do so at 06-24920758. About the company As an operator (day shifts), you will work for a producer and developer of high-quality innovative products in the specialty chemicals sector. These high-quality masterbatches are used in the plastics processing industry. Together with your team, you will work on the production of additive additives. These additives are used, among other things, in the paint and plastics processing, graphic, and cosmetic industries, as well as the electrical and electronic industry. They optimize surfaces and provide gloss or matt effects, for example. All additives are shipped worldwide from the warehouse. You will work at the location in Deventer, in a close-knit and enthusiastic team with a collegial and pleasant working atmosphere, alongside colleagues who work together daily. During initial contact, we will tell you more about the company, working atmosphere, and this position. Of course, you can also contact us directly to get more information about the organization. Job requirements In addition to enjoying working in a day shifts system and collaborating in a team, you meet the following job requirements: MBO-level of education and thinking;

Experience as an operator or in a production environment;

Willingness to work day shifts;

Preferably in possession of a vapro (but not required), Basic A diploma or B diploma is a plus;

A valid forklift certificate for moving raw materials (if you do not have one, we offer the opportunity to obtain it free of charge through Start People). What we offer you In addition to a dynamic job with a lot of responsibility, you will receive: Salary scales depend on age, knowledge, and experience, ranging from €2200 to €2700 based on a full-time position. You will also receive 8.33% vacation pay, a good travel allowance, and 25 vacation days;

We offer a structural full-time job at an organization that is dynamic, growing, innovative, and financially healthy;

Initially, you will be offered a temporary employment contract through Start People, but we are looking for our future employees. Therefore, we intend to offer a permanent employment contract. They are also open to a secondment agreement;

We offer the opportunity to obtain your forklift certificate free of charge;

You will have a lot of freedom and responsibility in your work and numerous training and development opportunities. Your input is very important to this company. We are looking for candidates who want to think, optimize, and improve processes. We look forward to receiving your response and application! You can do so by applying via the application button. Do you have any questions before you click the button? Feel free to call 053 481 4600 (option 3) Sanne or Sophie will be happy to assist you. Are you busy during the day and would you prefer to send a WhatsApp message in the evening? You can do so at 0624920758. We will then contact you at a suitable time for you."

What you will do
You will contribute to the maintenance of the sewer system in Purmerend and Beemster every day. Various construction and maintenance tasks are what you will carry out. This includes assisting with unclogging, the construction and maintenance of sewer systems, and making sewer connections. Additionally, you will handle notifications and assist citizens when necessary. If you enjoy working outdoors with your colleagues and are willing to get your hands dirty, then this position is perfect for you! The residents of Purmerend and Beemster are increasingly influencing their own living environment, and the municipality encourages their involvement and participation. We do not follow a clear plan or timetable. Each target group in the neighborhood or district faces its own challenges, and personalized solutions are expected from you that fit the neighborhood and its residents. 

About the company
At the municipalities of Purmerend and Beemster, we place the community at the center and assess on a case-by-case basis what we can add and should add. As a result, our colleagues go out into the field, interact with residents, and assess the situation on the spot. We do not work strictly based on standards, but instead, we search for the most optimal solution. We work on the spatial and social development of the city, creating a city where people enjoy living and working. The outside world experiences a city that is clean, intact, and safe, with well-maintained green spaces. 

Job requirements
We require the following from you:
․ You have intermediate vocational education level (MBO);
․ You have extensive knowledge of the sewer system;
․ You feel jointly responsible for the progress and quality of the work;
․ You think about how things can be improved or done differently;
․ You take initiative and are flexible;
․ You are willing to work on standby duty if necessary. 

What we offer you
From us, you can expect the following:
․ A full-time position with room for personal input and development;
․ A pleasant and informal work environment in a team that cares about Purmerend and Beemster;
․ Pay scale 5, maximum €2,711,- based on a 36-hour work week;
․ An individual choice budget (IKB) of 17.05%. This is 17.05% of your salary and consists of vacation money, year-end payment, life course contribution, and statutory leave. You can have your IKB paid out (monthly) or use it for leave, tax benefits for commuting, the bicycle scheme, trade union, and studies (if not reimbursed).

What you will do
Do you have experience as an Executive Secretary or Office Manager and do you only need one word? Is organizing and planning your second nature and do you have the ability to bring structure to the secretariat and improve things? Then we are looking for you! As an Executive Secretary, you are the well-known multitasker who supports the director and management team members in secretarial matters and also leads a secretary and receptionist. Your tasks include:
- Agenda management and handling emails;
- Organizing and taking minutes of meetings;
- Drafting reports and following up on assigned tasks;
- Organizing internal and external events;
- Reserving business lunches, meeting locations, dinners, and hotel stays;
- Improving processes within the secretariat and leading the team;
- Handling correspondence, presentations, reports, and management information. 
In short, a varied position in which you can fully utilize your organizational talent and administrative skills!
About the company
You will be part of a dynamic and growing family company in the Nijmegen region.
Job requirements
- You have intermediate vocational education (MBO+) or higher vocational education (HBO) level, supplemented with at least five years of relevant work experience;
- You are available for at least 32 hours per week;
- Naturally, you have a very good command of the Dutch language in both speech and writing and possess excellent communication skills;
- You can work well with the MS Office package and quickly pick up new software;
- You easily establish contact and are proactive;
- You are decisive and consistently prioritize correctly;
- You are analytically strong and enjoy improving processes and raising the level of service.
What we offer you
- A varied job that can be filled both part-time (32 hours per week) and full-time;
- A job with the prospect of a permanent contract;
- The salary indication is €3300 to €3900 gross per month based on 40 hours per week (including ADV surcharge), depending on age and experience;
- This is supplemented with 25 days of annual leave on a full-time basis, holiday pay, and a travel expense allowance;
- You have good opportunities for personal development;
- You can also take unlimited online courses via GoodHabitz.
Do you recognize yourself in the profile and are you open to a new challenge? Then we look forward to receiving your response! If you have any questions, you can also contact Rik Salemink at 024-382 81 05.

Job Description: Azure Cloud Architect/Developer Energy sector North Netherlands

Job Description: Is application development in the Cloud your passion, and Azure your expertise? Do you have an affinity for both old and new forms of energy? Would you like to help our clients in the Energy, Utility, and Manufacturing sectors with their digital transformation by (re)designing and implementing existing and new application functionality using Microsoft Azure technologies? Then read on!

What will you do? As an architect/developer in the energy sector at CGI, you will design, build, manage, and maintain mostly mission-critical applications and data platforms that run in the Azure Cloud and play a relevant role in the energy sector. Concepts such as energy source transport and management, measurement and monitoring, and transition will be part of your daily work. Our clients need stable, insightful, and well-functioning application and data environments. Will you help us design and build them?

As an Azure Cloud Architect/Developer, you will be part of a driven team of professionals within CGI. You are responsible, for example, for the design of one or more systems or data platforms and understand how these systems manifest themselves in the client's cloud landscape. You are able to provide our clients with sound advice in the field of cloud (application and service) architecture and can identify the advantages and disadvantages of a specific solution. This role requires communication and interaction with multiple development and testing teams, as well as with other architects and teams of the client. You act as the representative of the technical aspects of the (data) system in discussions with the client. Your tasks include:

- Aligning with domain architects and stakeholders to translate their input into a technical and secure solution;
- Developing the most efficient and smartest solution in Azure together with cloud and data professionals, developing application functionality, and making services available;
- Advising on improvement opportunities and identifying opportunities in the architecture of the clients you work with;
- Monitoring the costs of your applications and being able to justify them;
- Attending or contributing to the Architecture and Data & Analytics/DevOps practices of CGI;
- Following cloud and software development-related training to stay up to date with the latest developments.

What do you bring? You are customer-oriented, communicatively skilled, and have a profound love for application development. Your ambition primarily consists of the desire to grow (further) and to enjoy what you do. We offer plenty of room for self-development. Furthermore, you are analytical, sharp, and keep up with all developments in the field of cloud development. Do you have these characteristics? Then we only ask for the following:

- Minimum completed HBO (higher professional education) degree in the field of information management or computer science;
- You have a Microsoft certification and experience with Azure, Linux, and Kubernetes;
- You have a minimum of 3 years of experience as an architect or developer;
- You have experience with architecture methods such as TOGAF, SOA, and DYA;
- You have knowledge of agile methodologies;
- You can take on a directorial role in the creation of cloud strategies and solutions;
- You can write and design cloud migrations and modernize existing solutions;
- You have hands-on work experience with Azure tools such as Azure Data Factory, Synapse, or Power BI;
- Good command of the Dutch language, both oral and written.

Where will you end up? As an Azure Cloud Architect, you will work in the Energy, Utilities, and Manufacturing unit of North Netherlands. CGI helps the Netherlands take the lead in the energy transition and respond to the digitized solutions that are needed. Where energy is available in a sustainable and stable manner, efficiently and reliably regulated. Safe, taking into account European and national developments and the associated laws and regulations. In close cooperation with partners, shippers, and colleagues.

What do we offer? A direct permanent position with a competitive salary and the possibility to become a shareholder and participate in our successes. Through the CGI Academy, we offer the opportunity to continue developing yourself through education and training. You will have a place in our close-knit community where we share the responsibility of projects and exceed customer expectations together.

Are you ready to be part of our story? Apply now! We will contact you as soon as possible. Questions about the position? Ask John Fabriek (Director Consulting Services) via the "Apply now" button on this page or at 06 832 75 115. Questions about the application process? For more information, contact recruiter Lisa van der Kooij via (088) 564 0000 or via the "Apply now" button on this page. We do not work with external recruitment agencies. Therefore, we do not appreciate acquisition based on our vacancies.

