Job Description:
About the Position:
We are urgently looking for passionate Dutch teachers for a number of schools in the Amsterdam region. These are temporary positions (until the end of this school year) with the possibility of permanent employment. As an English teacher, you adapt your teaching material to the students' level and their world. You also know how to motivate unmotivated students and challenge them to look beyond their own limitations. You are well-informed about developments in your field and incorporate this knowledge into your lessons. Thanks to you, they are well-prepared for their exams. Having subject knowledge is not enough; it is important how you convey your expertise and enthusiasm for your subject. You play an important role in the overall development of young people and strive to bring out the best in every student. Are you eager to be in the classroom? Do you live near Amsterdam and can't wait to start working as a Dutch teacher? Apply now! Maandag® Education Amsterdam frequently receives requests from schools in the region to fill temporary and permanent positions. Therefore, we are constantly looking for teachers who enjoy variety and working at different schools. We also offer retired teachers the opportunity to return to work and take on various assignments through a permanent employment contract. Long-term assignments are definitely possible. Career changers are always welcome at Maandag® too! Job Requirements:
This is what you bring:
- A first or second degree qualification with relevant work experience;
- If you are in the final phase of your education, you can also start working with us;
- Available immediately for the 2022-2023 school year;
- Minimum availability of 0.4 FTE. Maandag® offers you:
