What you will do
Do you have knowledge of scanning activities, can you work accurately, and do you enjoy working in a friendly team? Then this position as Scan Operator at the Judicial Information Service (JustID) is for you! In the position of Scan Operator, you will prepare for scanning activities and ensure their correct execution. You do this by:
- Receiving and checking batches (bags, crates, boxes) of files to be scanned;
- Matching the actual number of received batches with the planning data;
- Verifying that the correct files have been received in terms of number, name, and coding;
- Investigating and reporting any differences in an administrative manner;
- Preparing files and documents for scanning, i.e. checking for sufficient cleaning (removal of staples, clips, non-standard sizes, etc.);
- Entering files/documents in batches;
- Checking during and after the scanning process for correct and complete processing of batches;
- Performing corrective actions where possible (additional scans);
- Checking and, if necessary, cleaning scanning equipment.

Together with the team, you will perform these tasks in a friendly and informal working environment, collaborating with people from the target group.

