You will be working at the Judicial Information Service. The Judicial Information Service is part of the Ministry of Justice and Security and contributes to providing an honest and comprehensive personal profile in the criminal justice chain by providing chain partners with a system of basic facilities for exchanging, storing, and providing evidence with information. Complete scanning facilities have been set up in Zutphen, allowing large quantities of documents to be scanned in a very short time. The scanning facility is equipped with scanners for digitizing loose-leaf objects and book scanners, which digitize the scan object in its original form. In addition, the digital documents can be provided with metadata to facilitate searching in the archive.

